PHIS Host for Debian
====================

Install layout
--------------

- Binary: `/usr/bin/phis-host`
- Default host config path: `/var/lib/phis/phis-host/config.json`
- Stage documentation path: `/var/lib/phis/phis-host/stages/README.md`
- Example config: `/usr/share/doc/phis-host/examples/phis-host.example.json`

This package depends on the packaged `phis` runtime and CLI. `phis-host` calls
`/usr/bin/phis` for stage-aware config inspection and copies the bundled
`phis-config.json` from the installed `phis` package during `stage init`.

Host state
----------

No runtime state is stored under `/etc/phis-host`.

Mutable host-side state belongs under:

- `/var/lib/phis/phis-host/`
- `/srv/phis/stages/<stage>/`

The package creates `/var/lib/phis/phis-host` and `/var/lib/phis/phis-host/stages`
on install. Per-stage roots are created by `phis-host stage init`.

Database bootstrap
------------------

`phis-host stage init db` uses the external `psql` client for PostgreSQL
bootstrap. If local database bootstrap is needed on the host, install
`postgresql-client` or an equivalent package that provides `psql`.
